[1]
Date: Wed 19 Jan 2005
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: World Health Organization (WHO), CSR, Disease Outbreak Report, Wed
19 Jan 2005 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2005_01_19b/en/>

Viet Nam: avian influenza situation - WHO update 4
-----------------------------------------------
WHO is aware of reports of a new laboratory-confirmed case of influenza A
(H5) virus infection in a 42-year-old man from Hanoi. The patient is alive,
but his older brother, a 45-year-old man from Thai Binh province, fell ill
in early January [2005] and subsequently died of a respiratory illness.
Laboratory tests on the deceased man are reportedly negative for influenza
A (H5) virus infection. WHO is seeking confirmation from the Ministry of
Health.
The Ministry of Health is conducting epidemiological investigations into
these cases, and WHO will keep in close contact with the Ministry of Health
over the progress and findings of these investigations.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[As of Wed 19 Jan 2005
<http://www.who.int/csr/disease/avian_influenza/country/cases_table_2005_01_19/en/>,
the WHO lists the cumulative number of confirmed human cases of avian
influenza A (H5N1) virus infection in East Asia since 28 Jan 2004 as 51 (17
in Thailand and 34 in Viet Nam), of whom, 37 have died (12 in Thailand and
25 in Viet Nam). - Mod.CP]
